(1874, 'Gazda želi sretan kraj', 'The Boss Wants a Happy End', 505, 'gazda1112', 'gazda1112en', '<p>Gazda želi sretan kraj\r\n</p><p>\r\nIsfendijar šalje Sinana u Kapadokiju da napiše scenarij za romantičnu komediju. Sinan je u teškoj poziciji jer ne zna šta bi mogao napisati. Šef vrši pritisak na njega da što prije završi svoj posao. Sinan upoznaje Ejlul, kćerku vlasnika hotela u kojem je smješten i ona mu se mnogo dopadne. Eylul ga inspiriše i odlučuje na njoj bazirati scenarij koji piše. Međutim, tu postoji problem: Ejlul je vjerenica poznatog glumca Faruka. Faruk i Sinan se dugo poznaju ali njihovo poznanstvo se baš i ne veže za lijepe uspomene. Sinan je, nekada bliskom prijatelju Faruku preoteo djevojku; zbog toga je Faruk Sinana proglasio neprijateljem.   </p>\r\n', '<p>The Boss Wants a Happy End\n</p><p>\nSinan is sent to Capadoccia by Isfendiyar to write a screenplay for a romantic comedy. Sinan is in a bad situation because he doesn''t have a clue what  to write about. His boss urges him to finish his job as soon as possible. Sinan meets Eylül, the daughter of  the owner of the hotel where he is staying and he is impressed by her. She even inspires him and he decides to write the screenplay based on her. But there is a problem: Eylül is the fiance of a famous actor Faruk. Faruk and Sinan have been knowing each other for a long time but their acquaintance is not really full of nice memories. Because Sinan has stolen the girlfriend of his once close friend Faruk; for this reason Faruk has proclaimed Sinan his enemy. </p>\n', '', '+387 33 668 186', '2016-12-11 20:00:00', 1, 'info@kinomeetingpoint.ba', 1, 0, 0),
