(1899, 'U Zvorniku ja sam ostavio svoje srce', 'In Zvornik I Have Left My Heart', 305, 'zvornik2712', 'zvornik2712en', '<p>U Zvorniku ja sam ostavio svoje srce\r\n</p><p>\r\nTekst jednog od najpoznatijih bh. pisaca Abdulaha Sidrana U Zvorniku ja sam ostavio svoje srce nesumnjivo spada u sam vrh domaćeg dramskog stvaralaštva. To je tekst koji koji govori o samom početku rata u BiH, o mučnoj golgoti koju su ljudi iz istočne Bosne prolazili samo radi razlike u imenu i prezimenu. O nadi i beznađu. Radnja drame odvija se u Zvorniku, pred sami početak rata. Rudo, nastavnik muzike i horovođa, je amater dirigent koji sanja da jednog dana napiše simfoniju o rijeci Drini, inspirisan Smetaninom Vltavom. Prilikom povratka s jednog takmičenja školskih horova, Rudo svoje učenike šalje natrag u Sarajevo, a on svraća u svoj rodni Zvornik. </p>\r\n', '<p>In Zvornik I Have Left My Heart\r\n</p><p>\r\nThe text of one of the most popular BH. writers Abdulah Sidran In Zvornik I Have Left My Heart undoubtedly one of the top domestic dramatic art. This is a text that speaks of the beginning of the Bosnian war, have seen the Golgotha that people from eastern Bosnia passed only for the difference in the first and last name. About the hope and hopelessness. The play takes place in Zvornik, just before the war. Rudo, a music teacher and choirmaster, is an amateur conductor who dreams of one day write a symphony about the Drina River, inspired Smetana Vltava. Upon returning from one competition of school choirs, Rudo his disciples sent back to Sarajevo, and he draws in his native Zvornik. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2016-12-27 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
