(2313, 'Omer i Merima', 'Omer and Merima', 100, 'omer3101', 'omer3101en', '<p>Omer i Merima\r\n</p><p>\r\nVelika i nezaboravna ljubav dvoje mladih opisana u baladi Omer i Merima bila je najveća inspiracija za kreiranje ove baletne predstave. Po prvi put na našoj baletnoj sceni donosimo jednu od najpoznatijih i najljepših bosanskohercegovačkih lirskih pjesama koja zasigurno spada u sam vrh najznačajnijih djela naše narodne poezije. Priča je to o čežnji, nadi i očekivanju nikada ispunjenog sna. Balada Omer i Merima kao dragulj naše kulturne baštine sinonim je jednog vremena, ali i metafora jedne univerzalne i svevremene ljubavi. </p>\r\n', '<p>Omer and Merima\r\n</p><p>\r\nGreat and unforgettable love young couple described in the ballad of Omer and Merima was the biggest inspiration for this ballet. For the first time on our ballet scene bringing one of the most beautiful Bosnian lyrical songs that certainly belongs to the top of the most important works of our national poetry. It is a story of longing, hope and anticipation never fulfilled dream. The Ballad of Omer and Merima as a jewel of our cultural heritage is a synonym of an era, but also a metaphor for a universal and timeless love.</p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 226 431', '2017-01-31 19:30:00', 3, 'info@nps.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2314, 'Žaba', 'Frog', 305, 'zaba0901', 'zaba0901en', '<p>Žaba\r\n</p><p>\r\nŽaba je priča o svima nama, ljudima današnjeg vremena, dobu nerazumijevanja i usamljenosti i potrage za ljubavlju i smislom. Predstava na gotovo hirurški način dijagnosticira vrijeme u kojem živimo. Ona donosi likove koji se ne snalaze u tranzicijskom vremenu i dobu promijenjenih vrijednosti. Tekst se bavi problemima današnjeg vremena koji su isti ili slični u BiH, Hrvatskoj ili Srbiji. To je prvenstveno problem nepostojanja komunikacije i nemogućnosti da čujemo tuđe mišljenje. Ovaj tekst ima jednu sjajnu tezu, a to je da uvijek u svemu tražimo krivca, propuštajući da sami napravimo bitne promjene u svojim životima. Zbog stvari, poput pitanja loših života i situacije u kojoj živimo, u stalnoj smo potrazi za krivcima, pa ih nalazimo u vlasti, u sistemu, direktoru firme, šefu, poslovođi, treneru, selektoru, umjesto da se za sebe sami izborimo. Moramo se umiješati u vlastite sudbine, umjesto što nad njima samo žalimo. </p>\r\n', '<p>Frog\r\n</p><p>\r\nThe frog is the story of all of us, the people of our time, the time of misunderstanding and loneliness and the search for love and meaning. The performance on almost surgical manner diagnosed the time in which we live. It brings the characters who are struggling in the transition period and age modified values. The text deals with the problems of the present time that are the same or similar in BiH, Croatia and Serbia. This is primarily a problem of lack of communication and inability to hear someone else''s opinion. This has a great theory, but it is not always in everything we are looking for the culprit, failing to make their own major changes in their lives. Due to the fact, such as the issue of bad life situations in which we live, we are constantly looking for the culprits, but they are in government, the system, the director of the company, boss, manager, coach, selector, rather than for himself alone fight. We need to intervene in their own destiny, rather than over them only regret. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-09 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2315, 'Ljupaf', 'Ljupaf', 305, 'ljupaf1001', 'ljupaf1001en', '<p>Ljupaf\r\n</p><p>\r\nKomedija Murraya Schisgala, LJUPAF, govori o ljudskim odnosima. Konkretno, riječ je o dvojici školskih prijatelja – neprilagođenom Harriju i materijalističkom oportunistu, Miltu –koji se ponovno susreću jednoga dana kada Milt spriječi Harrija u pokušaju da skoči sa bruklinskog mosta. Obojica pronalaze način da riješe vlastiti problem tako što jedan drugoga ponovno vrate u život, a Milt u Harriju vidi priliku da ostvari svoje planove. On želi ostaviti svoju ženu Ellen zbog druge i namješta priliku da Harry upozna njegovu ženu. Kada se Harry i Ellen upoznaju, oni se zaljube jedno u drugo, ali ubrzo Ellen i Milt shvate da su ipak njih dvoje stvoreni jedno za drugo i oni se ponovno spajaju u njihovoj ljupafi. </p>\r\n', '<p>Ljupaf\r\n</p><p>\r\nComedy Murray Schisgala, LJUPAF, talking about human relationships. In particular, it is about two school friends - unadjusted to Harry and materialistic opportunist, Milt -that meet again one day when Milt prevent Harry in an attempt to jump from the Brooklyn Bridge. They both find a way to solve its own problem by one another again return to life, and Milt Harrah see the opportunity to realize their plans. He wants to leave his wife Ellen for others and adjusts the chance that Harry meets his wife. When Harry and Ellen meet, they fall in love, but soon Ellen and Milt realize that though the two of them made for each other and they recombine in their ljupafi. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-10 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2316, 'Helem Nejse', 'Helem Nejse', 305, 'helem1101', 'helem1101en', '<p>Helem Nejse\r\n</p><p>\r\nKamerni teatar 55 osnovao je 1955. godine u Sarajevu veliki pozorišni reditelj, producent i teoretičar, Jurislav Korenić, u traganju za novim teatarskim izrazom, te iz potrebe za drugačijim teatarskim profilom od onoga koji je preovladavao u većini pozorišta tadašnje Jugoslavije. Taj novi, inovativan i tragalački pristup u teatarskoj produkciji predstavljao je stremljenje prema evropskoj avangardi toga vremena. Tokom godina, ovaj teatar je stekao veliki ugled koji je prevazišao granice Bosne i Hercegovine kao teatar visokih umjetničkih standarda sa izuzetnim glumačkim ansamblom. U prosjeku oko 13.000 ljudi tokom godine pogleda naše predstave, a kapacitet dvorane Kamernog teatra je 160 mjesta. Svoje predstave igramo u svim zemljama regiona kao i u drugim državama Evrope. </p>\r\n', '<p>Helem Nejse\r\n</p><p>\r\nChamber Theatre 55 was founded in 1955 in Sarajevo great theater director, producer and theorist, Jurislav Korenić, in search of new theatrical expression, and of the need for a different theater profile than that prevailing in most theaters of the former Yugoslavia. This new, innovative and an inquiring approach to theater production was the tendency of the European avant-garde of the time. Over the years, the theater has gained a great reputation that has transcended the borders of Bosnia and Herzegovina as a theater of high artistic standards with exceptional acting ensemble. On average about 13,000 people during the year view of our performance, and capacity of the hall of Chamber Theatre has 160 seats. His performances playing in all countries of the region as well as in other countries of Europe. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-11 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2317, 'Kad bi naglas govorili', 'If we speak out loud', 305, 'naglas1301', 'naglas1301en', '<p>Kad bi naglas govorili\r\n</p><p>\r\nOva predstava se bavi likovima koje svakodnevno srećemo u haustorima, ispred zgrade, pored zgrade, svuda oko nas. Oni možda imaju iste probleme kao i mi, ali to nikad nećemo saznati jer smo prestali otvoreno pričati. Da, mi žučno pričamo o vremenu, politici, velikim temama – ali negdje u tim velikim temama smo se izgubili mi, mali ljudi. Mali ljudi sa nama velikim problemima. A, potrebno je samo malo hrabrosti, malo spremnosti da podijelimo pokoju emociju, intimu, sa ljudima oko nas, kako bi shvatili da svuda oko nas postoje osjećajna, ranjiva bića koja imaju iste probleme. Ljudska bića spremna i sposobna da nam pomognu, da nas usreće, da budu naši idealni partneri. </p>\r\n', '<p>If we speak out loud\r\n</p><p>\r\nThis play deals with the characters that we meet every day in the hallways, in front of the building, next to the building, all around us. They may have the same problems as we do, but it''ll never know because we stopped to talk openly. Yes, we are learning about the weather, politics, big issues - or somewhere in these big issues we''re lost, little people. Small people with us a lot of trouble. And, it only takes a little courage, a little willingness to share the odd emotion, intimacy, with the people around us, to realize that all around us there are sensitive, vulnerable beings who have the same problems. Human beings willing and able to help us, to make us happy, to be our ideal partners. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-13 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
