(2325, 'Radnja na uglu', 'Shop Around the Corner', 305, 'radnja2301', 'radnja2301en', '<p>Radnja na uglu\r\n</p><p>\r\nOva predstava predstavlja prelijepu i ljupku sliku istočne Evrope prije Drugog svjetskog rata. Prikazuje vrijeme kad su ljudi imali manire, poštovali sebe i druge, poštovali jezike kojima su govorili, kako svoj tako i jezike drugih. Ideja, narod, nacija, grupa tada je značila nešto. Nakon 1945. godine društvene, etičke i umjetničke karakteristike čovjeka su se promijenile i pojavila se politika i cinizam. Ono što sam želio pokazati ovom predstavom jeste da, ako je svijet prije opstao, to je moguće i sada, ali samo ako se fokusiramo na nekoliko pravila, principa, kao što je poštovanje drugih i različitih, solidarnost, briga prema jezicima. Ustvari mislim da ova predstava pokazuje šta Bosanci trebaju sada, to je mirna i duhovita priča, s lijepim emocijama i nježnim osjećajima. To će dati nadu ljudima u ovim vremenima podjele. </p>\r\n', '<p>Shop Around the Corner\r\n</p><p>\r\nThis performance represents a beautiful and lovely picture of Eastern Europe before World War II. Displays the time when people had manners, respect themselves and others, respect for languages that are spoken of how his and other languages. Ideas, people, nation, group then meant something. After 1945, the social, ethical and artistic characteristics of man have changed and there was a policy and cynicism. What I wanted to show this play is that, if the world survived before, it is possible now, but only if we focus on a few rules, principles, such as respect for others and different, solidarity, care for languages. In fact I think this performance shows what Bosnians need now, it''s quiet and humorous story, with beautiful emotions and tender feelings. This will give hope to the people in these times of division. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-23 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2326, 'Bajka koju idiot priča', 'Fairy tale story idiot', 305, 'bajka2401', 'bajka2401en', '<p>Bajka koju idiot priča\r\n</p><p>\r\nBajka koju idiot priča govori o izgubljenom identitetu. Nepoznati čovjek se budi na onom svijetu i shvata da se ne sjeća ko je. Prilaze mu Bog i predstavnici raznih ideologija i svjetonazora i pokušavaju ga obrlatiti da ode sa njima. Da pristane na njihova pravila. Da zaboravi ko je i prihvati nametnutu i ponuđenu verziju sebe i svjetonazora. Da se potčini. Da se odrekne sebe. Borba traje do samoga kraja, a rezultat je u najmanju ruku neočekivan. Barem po bogove. </p>\r\n', '<p>Fairy tale story idiot\r\n</p><p>\r\nFairy tale idiot story tells of a lost identity. Unidentified man wakes up in the hereafter, and realizes that he can not remember when. Is approached by God and representatives of various ideologies and world views and trying to charm your go with them. To agree to their rules. To forget when and accept imposed and the offered version of yourself and world views. In order to subdue. To give up yourself. The fight lasts until the very end, and the result is the least unexpected. At least the gods. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-24 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2327, 'U Zvorniku ja sam ostavio svoje srce', 'In Zvornik I Have Left My Heart', 305, 'zvornik2501', 'zvornik2501en', '<p>U Zvorniku ja sam ostavio svoje srce\r\n</p><p>\r\nTekst jednog od najpoznatijih bh. pisaca Abdulaha Sidrana U Zvorniku ja sam ostavio svoje srce nesumnjivo spada u sam vrh domaćeg dramskog stvaralaštva. To je tekst koji koji govori o samom početku rata u BiH, o mučnoj golgoti koju su ljudi iz istočne Bosne prolazili samo radi razlike u imenu i prezimenu. O nadi i beznađu. Radnja drame odvija se u Zvorniku, pred sami početak rata. Rudo, nastavnik muzike i horovođa, je amater dirigent koji sanja da jednog dana napiše simfoniju o rijeci Drini, inspirisan Smetaninom Vltavom. Prilikom povratka s jednog takmičenja školskih horova, Rudo svoje učenike šalje natrag u Sarajevo, a on svraća u svoj rodni Zvornik. </p>\r\n', '<p>In Zvornik I Have Left My Heart\r\n</p><p>\r\nThe text of one of the most popular BH. writers Abdulah Sidran In Zvornik I Have Left My Heart undoubtedly one of the top domestic dramatic art. This is a text that speaks of the beginning of the Bosnian war, have seen the Golgotha that people from eastern Bosnia passed only for the difference in the first and last name. About the hope and hopelessness. The play takes place in Zvornik, just before the war. Rudo, a music teacher and choirmaster, is an amateur conductor who dreams of one day write a symphony about the Drina River, inspired Smetana Vltava. Upon returning from one competition of school choirs, Rudo his disciples sent back to Sarajevo, and he draws in his native Zvornik. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-25 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2328, 'Žaba', 'Frog', 305, 'zaba2601', 'zaba2601en', '<p>Žaba\r\n</p><p>\r\nŽaba je priča o svima nama, ljudima današnjeg vremena, dobu nerazumijevanja i usamljenosti i potrage za ljubavlju i smislom. Predstava na gotovo hirurški način dijagnosticira vrijeme u kojem živimo. Ona donosi likove koji se ne snalaze u tranzicijskom vremenu i dobu promijenjenih vrijednosti. Tekst se bavi problemima današnjeg vremena koji su isti ili slični u BiH, Hrvatskoj ili Srbiji. To je prvenstveno problem nepostojanja komunikacije i nemogućnosti da čujemo tuđe mišljenje. Ovaj tekst ima jednu sjajnu tezu, a to je da uvijek u svemu tražimo krivca, propuštajući da sami napravimo bitne promjene u svojim životima. Zbog stvari, poput pitanja loših života i situacije u kojoj živimo, u stalnoj smo potrazi za krivcima, pa ih nalazimo u vlasti, u sistemu, direktoru firme, šefu, poslovođi, treneru, selektoru, umjesto da se za sebe sami izborimo. Moramo se umiješati u vlastite sudbine, umjesto što nad njima samo žalimo. </p>\r\n', '<p>Frog\r\n</p><p>\r\nThe frog is the story of all of us, the people of our time, the time of misunderstanding and loneliness and the search for love and meaning. The performance on almost surgical manner diagnosed the time in which we live. It brings the characters who are struggling in the transition period and age modified values. The text deals with the problems of the present time that are the same or similar in BiH, Croatia and Serbia. This is primarily a problem of lack of communication and inability to hear someone else''s opinion. This has a great theory, but it is not always in everything we are looking for the culprit, failing to make their own major changes in their lives. Due to the fact, such as the issue of bad life situations in which we live, we are constantly looking for the culprits, but they are in government, the system, the director of the company, boss, manager, coach, selector, rather than for himself alone fight. We need to intervene in their own destiny, rather than over them only regret. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-26 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2329, 'Naš razred', 'Our class', 305, 'razred2701', 'razred2701en', '<p>Naš razred\r\n</p><p>\r\nSudbine desetero učenika jednog razreda, Našeg razreda, petero Poljaka i petero Židova, pratimo od davne 1935. pa sve do danas. Postajemo svjedoci njihovog odrastanja, prvih ljubavi, prijateljstava koja se raspadaju pod pritiskom okolnosti, nesretnih brakova, iznevjerenih očekivanja, ali i silovanja, ubojstava, lažnih svjedočenja – i sve nam to otkriva naličje zamršenih odnosa židovske i poljske zajednice, što i jest tema ovog komada.\r\nDogađaj koji pisac bira kao okosnicu priče historijska je činjenica. Naime, 10. jula 1941., u malom mjestu Jedwabno, u vrijeme njemačke okupacije, grupa mještana, Poljaka, upala je u domove svojih susjeda, Židova, zatvorila svoje dojučerašnje prijatelje u štalu i žive spalila. Njih 1600. A ova predstava pokazuje i prokazuje, prateći sudbinu desetero školskih kolega, kako je taj pogrom, pitanje krivnje pa čak broj žrtava okrutno podložan različitim tumačenjima ovisno o smjenama vlasti, promjenama režima, političkim interesima. Svako je novo vrijeme uzimalo za pravo proglasiti novu, svoju istinu. I uvijek nekom drugom zalijepiti krivnju na čelo. Jer krivi su uvijek samo oni – drugi. Odgovornost nikad nije u modi krojačima historije. </p>\r\n', '<p>Our class\r\n</p><p>\r\nFate of ten students of a class, our class, five Poles and five Jews, we follow from remote 1935 until today. We become witnesses of their growing up, first love, friendships that are falling apart under the pressure of circumstances, unhappy marriages, the expectations, as well as rape, murder, false testimony - and all of us to reveal reverse complicated relations of the Jewish and Polish communities, which is the subject of this piece .\r\nThe event writer chosen as the backbone of the story is a historical fact. On 10 July 1941, in the small village of Jedwabno, during the German occupation, a group of locals, Poles, broke into homes of their neighbors, the Jews, shut their erstwhile friends in a barn and burned alive. They 1600. And this play shows and denounces, following the fate of a dozen classmates, as the pogrom, the question of guilt and even the number of victims of cruel subject to different interpretations depending on the shifts authority to change the regime, political interests. Each new time were taking the right to declare a new, their truth. And still another stick the blame on his forehead. Because they always blame only those - others. Responsibility is never in fashion tailors history. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-27 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
(2330, 'Sluškinje', 'Maids', 305, 'sluskinje2801', 'sluskinje2801en', '<p>Sluškinje\r\n</p><p>\r\nPredstava se na jednom dubljem nivou tiče savremenog čovjeka u zemlji i uslovima u kojima živimo; klasnoj podjeljenosti,statusa moći i sudbinskoj određenosti kroz vizuru dvije žene koje nemaju ništa, a njihovo statusno određenje i posao ih stavljaju u nezavidnu situaciju potlačenih, poniženih i degradiranih. </p>\r\n', '<p>Maids\r\n</p><p>\r\nThe show is on a deeper level concerns of modern man in the country and the circumstances in which we live; class divisions, the status of power and fateful determination through the eyes of two women who have nothing but their status determination and the work they put in the unenviable situation of the oppressed, humiliated and degraded. </p>\r\n', '', '+387 33 550 475', '2017-01-28 20:00:00', 3, 'info@kamerniteatar55.ba', 1, 0, 1),
